Mathematical Morphisms

These are literal structure-preserving maps:

* Isomorphism — same structure.
* Homomorphism — preserves key operations.
* Endomorphism — map within the same system.
* Automorphism — symmetry of a system.
* Monomorphism — injective structure-preserving map.
* Epimorphism — surjective structure-preserving map.

These are fascinating because they already formalize what you’ve been calling translation while preserving invariants.

