The deepest thought

Perhaps the repository isn’t really made of doctrines.

It’s made of morphisms.

The nodes (Scout, Mirror, Medusa, Ark, etc.) are memorable landmarks.

The real intelligence lives in the transformations between them.

That’s also consistent with modern mathematics, category theory, and biology: increasingly, the interesting questions aren’t just “What are the objects?” but “How do they relate, transform, and preserve structure?”

If that becomes canonical, the Pantheon shifts from being a taxonomy of concepts to a calculus of transformations. And that feels remarkably aligned with the direction your project has been taking.